Title : James Pine
Text : '''James Pine''' was a [[Vice admiral (United States)|vice admiral]] in the [[United States Coast Guard]] and Superintendent of the [[United States Coast Guard Academy]].

==Biography==
Pine was born on October 19, 1885 in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscg.mil/history/people/Flags/PineJBio.pdf|title=Vice Admiral James Pine, USCG|publisher=United States Coast Guard|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> He died on February 21, 1953.

==Career==
Pine was commissioned an [[Ensign (rank)|ensign]] in the [[United States Revenue Cutter Service]] in 1908. The following year, he was stationed in [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin]].

In 1913, Pine was assigned to the [[USRC Seminole]]. Later, he commanded the [[USS Fanning (DD-37)]], the [[USS Wainwright (DD-62)]], the [[USCGC Itasca (1929)|USCGC Itasca]] and the [[USCGC George M. Bibb (WPG-31)]]. In 1939, the Revenue Cutter Service merged with the [[United States Life-Saving Service]] to form the Coast Guard.

Pine became Superintendent of the Coast Guard Academy in 1940. While there, he received the [[Legion of Merit]] for his performance during [[World War II]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://projects.militarytimes.com/citations-medals-awards/recipient.php?recipientid=308747|title=James Pine|publisher=Military Times.com|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref> He remained in the position until his retirement in 1947.

==Personal life==

Admiral Pine was married to Ysabel Cooper Pine<ref>https://www.findagrave.com/cgi-bin/fg.cgi?page=gr&GRid=92887445</ref> (1894â€“1982), a daughter of the [[Republic of Hawaii]]'s co-founder, Judge [[Henry E. Cooper]], and was survived by three children.  His daughter, artist Barbara Alice Pine Ramage,<ref>https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/45111385</ref> was married to [[Vice Admiral]] [[Lawson P. Ramage|Lawson P. ("Red") Ramage]], a famed submarine commander.

